Morris Goldstein, Appellant v. Henry Parker, Respondent. Decided March 4, 1890. Appeal from a judgment entered upon a dismissal of the complaint at the trial. Goodhardt & Phillips, for appellant. H. Joseph, for respondent.

Before Truax and Dugro, JJ.

The question involved was, whether the evidence was sufficient to carry the case to the jury. The Court held (Dugro J., writing, Truax, J., concurring), that it was not, and affirmed the judgment.
